  "prompt": "Can I send 500 and 1000 rs cash notes to India through USPS mail from USA?",
  "response": "Sending cash through the mail, including via USPS, is generally not advised and is often prohibited. The United States Postal Service (USPS) does not allow the mailing of cash, which includes currency notes like 500 and 1000 rupee notes. \n\nIf you're looking to send money to India, you may want to consider using services like bank transfers, wire transfers, or online remittance services that specialize in sending money internationally. These options are safer and more reliable than mailing cash. \n\nAdditionally, keep in mind that Indian regulations regarding cash sent from abroad can be strict, so it's essential to check the legalities and limits on remittances to India.",
